<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 13:10:23 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>人造“叶子”为无线生物医学设备提供动力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/artificial-leaf-powers-wireless-biomedical-device</link><description>植物通过光合作用有效地将光转化为能量——科学家和工程师仍然难以与电子设备相匹配的这种能力。最近，研究人员超越了传统的半导体材料，使用一种有前途的纳米等离子体材料来制造设备。这些微小的金属结构可以吸收和集中光能并产生高能电荷载流子。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/artificial-leaf-powers-wireless-biomedical-device.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 13:10:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/artificial-leaf-powers-wireless-biomedical-device</guid></item><item><title>一些患者群体更容易受到医疗人工智能近乎完美的隐私攻击</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/some-patient-groups-are-far-more-vulnerable-to-near-perfect-privacy-attacks-from-medical-ai</link><description>从胸部X光检查肺炎到评估皮肤黑斑是良性还是恶性，医疗人工智能系统在临床诊断中发挥着越来越重要的作用。不幸的是，用于训练这些人工智能系统的模型往往是网络攻击的受害者，特别是成员推理攻击（MIA），这可能导致人们的个人信息被窃取或泄露。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/some-patient-groups-are-far-more-vulnerable-to-near-perfect-privacy-attacks-from-medical-ai2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 12:55:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/some-patient-groups-are-far-more-vulnerable-to-near-perfect-privacy-attacks-from-medical-ai</guid></item><item><title>破纪录的 IBM 芯片使用技巧装入 1000 亿个晶体管</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/record-breaking-ibm-chip-uses-trick-to-cram-in-100-billion-transistors</link><description>IBM 最新芯片通过添加第二层硅电路，封装的晶体管数量是当前最先进芯片的两倍&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/record-breaking-ibm-chip-uses-trick-to-cram-in-100-billion-transistors.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 12:40:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/record-breaking-ibm-chip-uses-trick-to-cram-in-100-billion-transistors</guid></item><item><title>利用新技术在几秒钟内检测出危险气体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/detect-dangerous-gases-in-seconds-with-new-technology</link><description>一种被称为相干控制石英增强光声光谱的突破性方法已经被开发出来，可以快速检测和识别极低浓度的气体。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/detect-dangerous-gases-in-seconds-with-new-technology.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 12:25:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/detect-dangerous-gases-in-seconds-with-new-technology</guid></item><item><title>基因编辑研究表明，产生 ROS 的酶可指导植物细胞分裂和组织模式</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ros-producing-enzymes-guide-plant-cell-division-and-tissue-patterning-gene-editing-study-shows</link><description>细胞代谢过程中自然产生的活性氧（ROS）通常会对细胞造成氧化损伤。然而，这些分子在正常细胞信号传导中也发挥着重要作用。虽然ROS被确定为各种生物体中必需的信号分子，但它们在植物基本发育和形态发生中的确切作用仍不清楚。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ros-producing-enzymes-guide-plant-cell-division-and-tissue-patterning-gene-editing-study-shows2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 12:10:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ros-producing-enzymes-guide-plant-cell-division-and-tissue-patterning-gene-editing-study-shows</guid></item><item><title>神经导航引导聚焦超声的组合……：神经外科</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/combination-of-neuronavigation-guided-focused-ultrasound-neurosurgery</link><description>这是一项前瞻性、单臂、开放标签的试点试验。主要终点是 6 个月无进展生存期 (PFS)。根据独立放射学审查的神经肿瘤学反应评估标准对疾病进展进行评估。使用液体衰减反转恢复序列来评估放射学反应，以比较 FUS 暴露区域与非暴露区域。在 FUS 处理之前和之后测量血浆游离 DNA (cfDNA) 浓度。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/combination-of-neuronavigation-guided-focused-ultrasound-neurosurgery2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 11:55:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/combination-of-neuronavigation-guided-focused-ultrasound-neurosurgery</guid></item><item><title>NANOG 在人类胚胎发生中的作用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/role-for-nanog-in-human-embryogenesis</link><description>新的研究表明，基因组编辑技术可用于改变人类胚胎细胞中的单个基因，从而能够以无与伦比的细节研究人类的早期发育。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/role-for-nanog-in-human-embryogenesis.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 11:40:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/role-for-nanog-in-human-embryogenesis</guid></item><item><title>太阳风暴意外地减少了宇宙射线通量</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/solar-storm-unexpectedly-reduces-cosmic-ray-flux</link><description>袭击地球的太阳风暴似乎减少了传入的高能宇宙射线的数量，这提出了一种测量太阳活动的新方法。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/solar-storm-unexpectedly-reduces-cosmic-ray-flux.jpg" /&gt; 由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 11:25:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/solar-storm-unexpectedly-reduces-cosmic-ray-flux</guid></item><item><title>激光捕获的金属氢化物分子开辟了通向超冷氢的道路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/metal-hydride-molecule-trapped-with-laser-light-opens-path-to-ultracold-hydrogen</link><description>用激光控制和捕获分子（由两个或多个化学结合原子组成的物质单元）比捕获单个原子更具挑战性。这是因为分子表现出更复杂的振动和旋转动力学，这使得它们更难以冷却和捕获。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/metal-hydride-molecule-trapped-with-laser-light-opens-path-to-ultracold-hydrogen.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 11:10:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/metal-hydride-molecule-trapped-with-laser-light-opens-path-to-ultracold-hydrogen</guid></item><item><title>狗骨式设计有助于 2D 纳米带晶体管在宽度缩小时保持快速高效</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/dog-bone-design-helps-2d-nanoribbon-transistors-stay-fast-and-efficient-as-widths-shrink</link><description>晶体管是控制电流的小型半导体开关，是从计算机到智能手机、可穿戴设备、传感器和智能电器等所有电子设备的核心组件。在过去的几十年里，电子工程师一直致力于提高晶体管的速度和性能，同时缩小晶体管的尺寸。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dog-bone-design-helps-2d-nanoribbon-transistors-stay-fast-and-efficient-as-widths-shrink.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 10:55:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/dog-bone-design-helps-2d-nanoribbon-transistors-stay-fast-and-efficient-as-widths-shrink</guid></item></channel></rss>